       <script>
        $(document).ready(function() {
      // change the logo link to the main iste site
      $('#LogoLink').attr('href','https://www.iste.org/');

      // read the cart quantity cookie &amp; add next to cart if it's a number
      var cartQty = $.cookie('cartQty');
      if (!isNaN(cartQty)) {
        $('#auxNavCart &gt; span').html(cartQty);
      }

      // convert the landing page headers to sentence case (by default the content is all caps)
      $('.HLLandingControl h2').each(function(){
        var myString = ($(this).html().trim());
        myString = myString.toLowerCase().replace(/(^\s*\w|[\.\!\?]\s*\w)/g,function(c){return c.toUpperCase()});
        $(this).html(myString);
      });

      $('#searchBtn').on('click', function(e){
        e.preventDefault();
        $('#MPSearchBlock').slideToggle();
      });
      // add text to search button since we're no longer using an image
      $('#SearchControl_SearchWhole').attr('value','SEARCH');

      // get variables for link/text replacement in top aux nav bar
      if ($('#Welcome_NotLoggedIn').length) {
      // user is not logged in
        $('#profileProgress, #profileHelp').hide();
        //var loginLink = $('#Welcome_NotLoggedIn').html();
        var loginLink = '&lt;a href="https://www.iste.org/login"&gt;Register&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.iste.org/login"&gt;Sign In&lt;/a&gt;';
        $('#menuLinks').html(loginLink);
        // hide the complete profile help icon &amp; popup
        $('#Welcome_Details_HelpIcon_0, #Welcome_Details_ProfileHelp_0').css('display', 'none');
      }
      else {
      // user is logged in
        // get welcome text &amp; remove comma after "Welcome"
        var welcomeText = $('#Welcome_Content .Details h1').html().replace(',','');
        //var menuLinks = $('#Welcome_Content .Details .MenuLinks').html();
        //the above returns: &lt;a class="First" href="/connect/profile/?UserKey=ac98aa63-8b1e-43b8-ba43-2b55e563c5fe"&gt;Profile&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href="/HigherLogic/Security/Logout.aspx?ReturnURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.iste.org%2Flogout"&gt;Logout&lt;/a&gt;
        var logoutLink = $('#Welcome_Content .Details .MenuLinks a').not('a.First').attr('href');
        var menuLinks = '&lt;a href="' + logoutLink + '"&gt;Log Out&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.iste.org/join/my-profile"&gt;Profile&lt;/a&gt;';

        var completeProfileLink = $('#Welcome_Details_CompletProfile_0').attr('href');
        //var progressBarWidth = parseInt($('.ProgressBarProgress').css('width'));
        var progressBarWidth = $('.ProgressBarProgress').width();
        // 200px is the default unstyled total width of the progress bar
        var progressBarPct = progressBarWidth / 200;
        var newProgressBarWidth = parseInt(60 * progressBarPct) + 'px';
        $('#profileProgress &gt; span &gt; span').css('width', newProgressBarWidth);
        $('#menuLinks').html(menuLinks);
        // this is to replace the "profile" link url in the nav
        //$('#menuLinks a.First').attr('href','https://www.iste.org/membership/my-profile');
        // add a function to hide help if the icon is clicked
        $('#Welcome_Details_HelpIcon_0').on('click', function(e){
          e.preventDefault();
          $('#Welcome_Details_ProfileHelp_0').toggle();
        });
      }
      $('#welcomeText').html(welcomeText);

      // remove the old help icon and old help popup since we've replaced them
      $('img#Welcome_Details_HelpIcon_0, #Welcome_Details_ProfileHelp_0.Help').remove();
  });
       </script>

                  <script language="javascript" type="text/javascript">
                   var RadEditorMainCopy_ctl03_Editor = null;
    var restoreMainCopy_ctl03_Editor;

    function addVariableMainCopy_ctl03_Editor(sign) {
        var rtfEditor = RadEditorMainCopy_ctl03_Editor.get_html();
        RadEditorMainCopy_ctl03_Editor.set_html(rtfEditor + sign);
    }

    function OnClientLoadMainCopy_ctl03_Editor(editor) {
        RadEditorMainCopy_ctl03_Editor = editor;

        var element = document.all ? editor.get_document().body : editor.get_document();
        var htmlElement = editor.get_textArea();

        var symbolTool = editor.getToolByName("InsertSymbol");
        if (symbolTool != null) {
            symbolTool.set_updateHeader(false);
        }

        //******************************************************************************
        //* The following event handlers will be used in conjunction with 
        //* The EventAddEdit.ascx control to manage the dirty form status. If any of
        //* the following methods/events are fired, and the html text has changed;
        //* the RadEditorCurrentTxt field is populated with the current editor html text,
        //* a change event will be fired for the RadEditorCurrentTxt field. This is a
        //* hidden field located in the UI/Community/EventAddEdit.ascx control, and it's
        //* change event handler is located in the jquery.hl_community_event_creation.js 
        //* plugin.
        //******************************************************************************

        $telerik.addExternalHandler(element, "blur", function(e) {

            restoreMainCopy_ctl03_Editor = RadEditorMainCopy_ctl03_Editor.createRestorePoint();

            updateDirtyHtmlStatus(editor);
        });

        $telerik.addExternalHandler(htmlElement, "blur", function(e) {

            updateDirtyHtmlStatus(editor);
        });

        editor.attachEventHandler("onkeydown", function(e) {

            updateDirtyHtmlStatus(editor);
        });
        //******************************************************************************

        editor.get_contentArea().className = "RadContentArea";

        // to skip the tabbing of the tools included in the editor.
        // the tabbing (TabIndex) will go straight to the editor
        var buttonsHolder = $get(editor.get_id() + "Top");
        var buttons = buttonsHolder.getElementsByTagName("A");
        for (var i = 0; i &lt; buttons.length; i++) {
            var a = buttons[i];
            a.tabIndex = -1;
            a.tabStop = false;
        }

        // this is to fix radeditor height on chrome
        if ($.browser.chrome) {
            editor.sizer.setContentElementHeight = function () {
                var i = this.editor,
                    h = new Telerik.Web.UI.Editor.UI.DimensionsCalculator(i),
                    k = h.isContainerPxHeight(),
                    l = h._isPercentHeight(),
                    m = h._getSupportingUIHeight(),
                    f = h.containerHeight(),
                    g = f - m,
                    n = i.get_element(),
                    j = this.getIframe();
                if (f &lt; m + this.lineHeight) {
                    f = m + this.lineHeight;
                    if (k) {
                        n.style.height = f + "px";
                    }
                    g = this.lineHeight;
                }
                j.style.height = '100%'; // this is to make the iframe content height to 100%
                if (l) {
                    i.get_mainTable().style.height = f + "px";
                    this.percentHeightFirstLoad = l;
                }
                if (!this.editorHeight) {
                    this.editorHeight = f;
                }
            }
            $(editor.get_contentAreaElement()).css('height', '100%');
        }
    }

    //******************************************************************************
    //* The following event method will be used in conjunction with 
    //* The EventAddEdit.ascx control to manage the dirty form status. If any of
    //* the following methods/events are fired, and the html text has changed;
    //* the RadEditorCurrentTxt field is populated with the current editor html text,
    //* a change event will be fired for the RadEditorCurrentTxt field. This is a
    //* hidden field located in the UI/Community/EventAddEdit.ascx control, and it's
    //* change event handler is located in the jquery.hl_community_event_creation.js 
    //* plugin.
    //******************************************************************************
    function OnClientCommandExecutedMainCopy_ctl03_Editor(editor) {

        updateDirtyHtmlStatus(editor);
    }

//******************************************************************************

    function updateDirtyHtmlStatus(editor) {

        // The current RadEditor exists on the EventAddEdit.ascx control
        if (typeof ($("input[id*='RadEditorCurrentTxt']")) != "undefined") {

            // The RadEditor html has changed
            if ($("input[id*='RadEditorCurrentTxt']").val() != editor.get_html(true)) {

                // Update the RadEditorCurrentTxt field with the new html value
                $("input[id*='RadEditorCurrentTxt']").val(editor.get_html(true));

                // Fire the change event for the RadEditorCurrentTxt control.
                $("input[id*='RadEditorCurrentTxt']").change();
            }
        }
    }

    //******************************************************************************

    function OnClientPasteHtmlMainCopy_ctl03_Editor(sender, args) {
        var commandName = args.get_commandName();
        var text = args.get_value(); //get the pasted value   

        if ($telerik.isFirefox) {
            text = text.replace(/&lt;!--(.|\s)*?--&gt;/gi, ""); //strip the style tag content   
            args.set_value(text); //set the modified content in the editor   
        }
    }

    function PastePropertyMainCopy_ctl03_Editor(propertyName) {
        RadEditorMainCopy_ctl03_Editor.pasteHtml(propertyName);
    }
                  </script>

              <script language="javascript" type="text/javascript">
               $(document).ready(function() {
            
            initDiscussionsDropDownMainCopy_ctl13(); 
            
        });

        function initDiscussionsDropDownMainCopy_ctl13() {

            var listHeaderColor = hl_common_ui_getContrastYIQ($('.HLLandingControl h2').getHexBackgroundColor());
            var dropdownicon = 'https://d2x5ku95bkycr3.cloudfront.net/App_Themes/Common/Images/titleBarTriangleBlack.png';
            if (listHeaderColor == 'white') {
                dropdownicon = 'https://d2x5ku95bkycr3.cloudfront.net/App_Themes/Common/Images/titleBarTriangleWhite.png'
            }

            $("div[id$=MainCopy_ctl13_sortByToggle82eba6bc-1b3e-4322-b829-e20318959dcb]").hl_core_ui_dropDown({
                ObjClassContainer: 'HLLandingControl',
                ObjPositionCSS: 'ajaxifyhyperlinks',
                ToolTip: 'More Options',
                Icon: dropdownicon,
                IconWidth: '12px',
                IconHeight: '7px',
                IconPadding: '0 0 0 0',
                ContainerWidth: '20px',
                ContainerHeight: '20px',
                ContainerFloatOption: 'right',
                InsertIconAfterObject: '#MainCopy_ctl13_TitleText812301f3',
                AlternateText: 'Latest Discussions - More Options'
            });

            $('.LinkPostedIn').tipTip({ delay: 200 });
            $('.ContainerTableProfile').hl_util_ui_styleColumns();

            /**************************************/
            /*skin the ratings that are using star*/
            /**************************************/
            var $avg = $('.AverageRating').find(':first-child');

            $.each($avg, function(index, value) {
                if ($.trim($(value).text()) != '') {
                    var $txt = $.trim($(value).text());
                    var $div = $('&lt;div class="ratingSkinning"&gt;' + $txt + '&lt;/div&gt;');
                    var $apnd = '';

                    /*append extra verbiage to complete a lexicon*/
                    if ($txt.indexOf('Not') == -1) {
                        $apnd = ' have been made';
                    }

                    /*remove the roque text so it doesn't float to the right and above the stars*/
                    $(value).contents().filter(function() {
                        return this.nodeType === 3;
                    }).remove();

                    /*insert after star*/
                    $(value).css("margin", "8px 0 8px 0");
                    $($div).insertAfter($(value));
                    $($div).prop("title", $txt + $apnd);
                    $($div).tipTip({ delay: 200 });
                }
            });

            /**************************************/
            /*skin the ratings that are using the 
                      recommended feature $(value).css("padding", "2px 0");*/
            /**************************************/
            var $tot = $('.TotalRatingLike').find(':first-child span');

            $.each($tot, function(index, value) {
                var $a = $(value).find('a');
                var txt;

                var apnd = ' people have recommend this. Click the link to see them all';

                /*parse out the number for the recommends*/
                if (parseInt($($a).text())) {
                    txt = parseInt($($a).text()) + apnd;
                    $($a).prop('title', txt);

                    /*find any text that goes along with the recommend*/
                    if ($.trim($(value).text()) != '') {
                        var $spn = $('&lt;span /&gt;');
                        $($spn).prop("title", txt);

                        /*Depricated - get the text, remove the old and add to span so we can set a title*/
                        txt = $.trim($(value).contents(":not(a)").text());
                    }
                }
            });

        }
              </script>

                   <script type="text/javascript">
                    function showLikesModal(itemkey, likeModalId, titleText) {

                //find current div with contents, create container div above it
                var itemKeySelector = "#" + itemkey;
                var likeModalIdSelector = "#" + likeModalId;
                if ($(itemKeySelector).html() == "") {
                    return
                };
                var div = $("&lt;div title='" + titleText + "' id='" + itemkey + "'&gt;&lt;/div&gt;");
                $('body').append(div);
                $(itemKeySelector).html($(likeModalIdSelector).html());

                var buttonOpts = {};

                buttonOpts['Close'] = function() {
                    $(this).dialog("close");
                };

                //use dynamic container due to updatepanels
                $(itemKeySelector).dialog({
                    resizable: true,
                    height: 250,
                    width: 500,
                    modal: true,
                    buttons: buttonOpts

                });

                $(itemKeySelector).dialog('open');
            }
                   </script>

    <script>
     //remove on next telerik update
        (function ($, $E, undefined) {
            $.extend($E._PopupController.prototype, {
                _registerGlobalBodyEventHandlers: function () {
                    var configureFrameHandlers = function (toAttach, popupController) {
                        //Attach a listener to all frame elements on the page
                        var windowFrames = window.frames;

                        for (var i = 0; i &lt; windowFrames.length; i++) {
                            var windowDocument = null;

                            try {
                                windowDocument = windowFrames[i].document;
                            }
                            catch (e) { }

                            if (!windowDocument) {
                                continue;
                            }

                            //this try catch is needed because of security problems with Firefox and other iframes on the page
                            try {
                                if (toAttach !== false) {
                                    popupController.attachToDocument(windowDocument);
                                }
                                else {
                                    popupController.detachFromDocument(windowDocument);
                                }
                            }
                            catch (e) { }
                        }
                    }

                    //ESC handler      
                    var escHandler = Function.createDelegate(null, function (e) {
                        if (e.keyCode == 27) {
                            Telerik.Web.UI.Editor.PopupController.hideActivePopup();
                        }
                    });

                    //the $addHandler method was replaced with $telerik.addExternalHandler because it 
                    //causes a problem with disabled elements (especially the mousedown handler in this specific case)
                    $telerik.addExternalHandler(document.body, 'keydown', escHandler);
                    $telerik.addExternalHandler(document.body, 'mousedown', this._hideHandler);

                    //Dispose the global event handlers         
                    Sys.Application.add_unload(function () {
                        $telerik.removeExternalHandler(document.body, 'mousedown', Telerik.Web.UI.Editor.PopupController._hideHandler);
                        $telerik.removeExternalHandler(document.body, 'keydown', escHandler);
                        configureFrameHandlers(false, Telerik.Web.UI.Editor.PopupController); //Supply instance
                    });

                    configureFrameHandlers(true, this);
                },
            });
        })($telerik.$, Telerik.Web.UI.Editor);
    </script>
